WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.006 --> 00:00:08.008
[suspenseful music droning]

2
00:00:13.388 --> 00:00:18.018
WHITE CENTER
WORK JOURNAL

3
00:00:22.063 --> 00:00:24.024
- [soft meow]
- [man gasps]

4
00:00:25.066 --> 00:00:27.360
[girl] Director Obata? What are you doing?

5
00:00:27.444 --> 00:00:28.486
[Obata sighs]

6
00:00:30.238 --> 00:00:31.281
What's wrong?

7
00:00:32.240 --> 00:00:33.783
You shouldn't be out here.

8
00:00:39.289 --> 00:00:41.082
[girl] What were you burning?

9
00:00:42.375 --> 00:00:43.251
[Obata] Hmm?

10
00:00:46.004 --> 00:00:48.506
Don't worry.
It has nothing to do with you.

11
00:00:49.007 --> 00:00:51.509
- [girl] It does. though.
- [Obata] Huh.

12
00:00:52.385 --> 00:00:53.428
In what way?

13
00:00:54.596 --> 00:00:55.430
[girl meows]

14
00:00:57.182 --> 00:00:59.392
- [Obata gasps]
- [dramatic chord screeching]

15
00:01:05.106 --> 00:01:06.107
[Obata] Satsuki…

16
00:01:07.233 --> 00:01:10.195
It's dangerous out there.
Come back. Satsuki!

17
00:01:10.278 --> 00:01:13.281
Come back! It's dangerous! Satsuki!

18
00:01:13.990 --> 00:01:15.533
Stay away from there!

19
00:01:16.159 --> 00:01:17.619
Satsuki!

20
00:01:17.702 --> 00:01:19.996
Come back! It's dangerous! Hey!

21
00:01:20.497 --> 00:01:22.582
Come back! Please! Satsuki!

22
00:01:22.665 --> 00:01:25.877
- [woman] Director Ozaki!
- [Obata] Satsuki! Come back!

23
00:01:25.960 --> 00:01:27.879
- [woman] Director!
- [Obata] It's dangerous!

24
00:01:27.962 --> 00:01:30.006
- [woman] Wake up!
- [Obata] Satsuki!

25
00:01:30.548 --> 00:01:31.591
[woman] Director!

26
00:01:32.092 --> 00:01:33.301
[Obata] Come back!

27
00:01:33.802 --> 00:01:34.636
Satsuki!

28
00:01:34.719 --> 00:01:36.971
- [woman] Come back!
- [Obata] You'll hurt yourself.

29
00:01:37.680 --> 00:01:39.974
- Satsuki… Satsuki!
- Director. stop!

30
00:01:40.475 --> 00:01:42.769
Snap out of it! Wake up!

31
00:01:42.852 --> 00:01:44.687
- [woman breathes heavily]
- [Obata grunts]

32
00:01:44.771 --> 00:01:45.897
[Obata hesitates]

33
00:01:46.606 --> 00:01:48.191
- Are you all right?
- Yes. I'm fine.

34
00:01:48.274 --> 00:01:50.318
Let's get you back. You were sleepwalking.

35
00:01:51.528 --> 00:01:52.904
[Obata grunts]

36
00:01:52.987 --> 00:01:54.447
I'm all right. Really. I'm fine.

37
00:01:54.531 --> 00:01:56.074
- Are you sure?
- Yes. yes.

38
00:01:56.157 --> 00:01:57.534
PLACE OF REST: UMIKAZE

39
00:01:57.617 --> 00:01:59.327
- [indistinct chatter]
- [gentle piano music]

40
00:01:59.410 --> 00:02:02.288
- [man 1] Stop. That's dangerous! Don't!
- [man 2] Breakfast time!

41
00:02:02.372 --> 00:02:04.415
[man 1] You… Ah. ah. ah! Come here!

42
00:02:04.916 --> 00:02:06.709
- [man 2] Is it yummy?
- [man 1] I got you!

43
00:02:06.793 --> 00:02:10.130
- [man 2] Want any more soy sauce?
- [man 1] Leo. you're going to sit.

44
00:02:10.213 --> 00:02:12.048
Sit. Leo. sit.

45
00:02:12.132 --> 00:02:14.175
No. no. no. hey. Look what you did.

46
00:02:14.259 --> 00:02:15.593
You spilled your drink.

47
00:02:15.677 --> 00:02:17.387
- [man 2] I'll clean it up.
- Leo…

48
00:02:17.470 --> 00:02:19.013
Leo. Go ahead. thanks.

49
00:02:19.097 --> 00:02:21.099
[man 2] You all right. sweetie?
It didn't get on you?

50
00:02:21.182 --> 00:02:24.144
[man 1] Deep breaths. okay?
Let's just take a deep breath.

51
00:02:24.644 --> 00:02:27.147
Did something bad happen this morning?

52
00:02:27.230 --> 00:02:28.356
[Obata] Shota.

53
00:02:28.439 --> 00:02:30.066
Aren't you going to eat breakfast?

54
00:02:30.150 --> 00:02:32.235
Ah. no. thanks. sir. I'm fine.

55
00:02:33.278 --> 00:02:36.364
Oh! You can't forget your lunch. then.
Here.

56
00:02:36.447 --> 00:02:39.284
Oh. um. do you know
all the members of the G7?

57
00:02:39.367 --> 00:02:40.368
The G7?

58
00:02:40.869 --> 00:02:42.704
It's going to be on our test.

59
00:02:45.165 --> 00:02:49.252
There's the UK. France. Canada.

60
00:02:49.335 --> 00:02:51.045
Japan…

61
00:02:55.425 --> 00:02:56.467
[objects clattering]

62
00:02:56.551 --> 00:02:57.802
[man 1] Oh!

63
00:02:58.970 --> 00:03:00.847
America. Germany. and Italy. Okay. bye!

64
00:03:02.000 --> 00:03:08.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

65
00:03:09.606 --> 00:03:12.108
[Kyoko. on TV] <i>A man</i>
<i>calling himself the Human Vapor…</i>

66
00:03:12.192 --> 00:03:13.776
Leo ate most of his food.

67
00:03:13.860 --> 00:03:16.237
[woman] Oh. good. Finally. Thank you.

68
00:03:16.321 --> 00:03:17.989
[news continues on TV]

69
00:03:18.072 --> 00:03:21.951
[Kyoko] <i>The Metropolitan Police Department</i>
<i>arrived on the scene to secure the area</i>

70
00:03:22.035 --> 00:03:25.538
<i>and question the man. but he vanished</i>
<i>when a dense gust of fog blew through.</i>

71
00:03:25.622 --> 00:03:27.540
<i>knocking down police officers.</i>

72
00:03:27.624 --> 00:03:29.334
<i>The phenomenon was caught on camera.</i>

73
00:03:29.417 --> 00:03:31.377
<i>Just who is the Human Vapor.</i>

74
00:03:31.461 --> 00:03:33.171
<i>and what is the mysterious White Center?</i>

75
00:03:33.254 --> 00:03:36.633
<i>The investigation is still ongoing.</i>
<i>More to come.</i>

76
00:03:37.133 --> 00:03:39.177
<i>And let's take another look</i>
<i>at the dramatic footage</i>

77
00:03:39.260 --> 00:03:41.221
<i>captured exclusively by our reporters.</i>

78
00:03:42.180 --> 00:03:44.515
[Kyoko] <i>What were</i>
<i>these alleged crimes. exactly?</i>

79
00:03:45.099 --> 00:03:47.727
<i>White Center…</i>

80
00:03:49.604 --> 00:03:51.689
The Human Vapor. huh?

81
00:03:51.773 --> 00:03:53.024
That's a new one.

82
00:03:53.107 --> 00:03:56.277
[woman] He said. "White Center."
You heard of a place like that?

83
00:03:56.361 --> 00:03:57.904
[man] Can't say that I have.

84
00:03:58.404 --> 00:04:00.990
<i>The people who were involved</i>
<i>with White Center</i>

85
00:04:01.074 --> 00:04:04.744
<i>must be remembering</i>
<i>the crimes they committed and panicking….</i>

86
00:04:04.827 --> 00:04:07.622
- [dish clatters]
- [woman gasps] Oh. that scared me.

87
00:04:08.248 --> 00:04:10.083
- [man and woman chuckle]
- [man] Mr. Ozaki?

88
00:04:10.166 --> 00:04:12.168
[woman] Director. are you all right?
Director Ozaki?

89
00:04:12.252 --> 00:04:14.879
<i>This is my solemn vow</i>
<i>to all those guilty souls.</i>

90
00:04:15.713 --> 00:04:17.632
<i>I'm going to kill you all.</i>

91
00:04:18.633 --> 00:04:21.135
<i>one by one.</i>

92
00:04:21.219 --> 00:04:23.221
[suspenseful music playing]

93
00:04:25.974 --> 00:04:27.976
[dark. dramatic music playing]

94
00:05:04.846 --> 00:05:10.310
HUMAN VAPOR

95
00:05:10.393 --> 00:05:14.689
[detective] Then you went to where
Bunko Ramen used to be 27 years ago.

96
00:05:14.772 --> 00:05:16.607
What I don't understand is how you knew

97
00:05:16.691 --> 00:05:19.277
the Human Vapor
would hold the press conference there.

98
00:05:19.360 --> 00:05:20.486
of all places.

99
00:05:21.279 --> 00:05:24.907
He never turned up at the other location.
so I connected the dots.

100
00:05:25.408 --> 00:05:29.495
Or… perhaps another reliable source
reached out to you?

101
00:05:29.579 --> 00:05:32.081
Tipped you off
so you could arrive in time?

102
00:05:32.582 --> 00:05:34.292
I assure you. I have no such source.

103
00:05:34.375 --> 00:05:37.837
All right.
Did the culprit himself contact you. then?

104
00:05:38.796 --> 00:05:41.174
I find it hard to believe
you two have no connection.

105
00:05:41.257 --> 00:05:42.925
Okay. listen.

106
00:05:44.761 --> 00:05:46.763
Why don't you just cut to the chase?

107
00:05:48.931 --> 00:05:51.225
[quiet. tense music playing]

108
00:05:51.309 --> 00:05:54.187
[detective sighs]
It's not that I don't believe you.

109
00:05:55.021 --> 00:05:57.065
but we have to explore every angle.

110
00:05:57.148 --> 00:05:59.150
[tense music playing]

111
00:06:07.408 --> 00:06:08.868
[Kenji sighs]

112
00:06:16.084 --> 00:06:18.211
4 MONTHS AGO

113
00:06:18.294 --> 00:06:21.464
You say you've never been to the hotel
where the victim of the drug overdose

114
00:06:21.547 --> 00:06:22.590
was found.

115
00:06:23.132 --> 00:06:24.926
So where were you that night?

116
00:06:27.178 --> 00:06:28.179
[attorney] Mori?

117
00:06:33.518 --> 00:06:35.353
I choose to remain silent.

118
00:06:37.188 --> 00:06:40.024
You offered the young. inebriated victim
a drive home.

119
00:06:40.108 --> 00:06:43.694
- You put her in the vehicle. right?
- I choose to remain silent.

120
00:06:46.531 --> 00:06:49.951
You choose to remain silent.
so you don't wanna talk?

121
00:06:50.493 --> 00:06:51.702
Then I'll fill in the blanks.

122
00:06:51.786 --> 00:06:55.623
You drugged a 17-year-old high-school girl
and killed her. and have nothing to say?

123
00:06:55.706 --> 00:06:57.792
- [Mori] What? You have no evidence!
- Hold on.

124
00:06:58.459 --> 00:07:01.462
You're grasping at straws.
You have nothing. Nothing!

125
00:07:06.509 --> 00:07:08.678
I know you were once yakuza.

126
00:07:09.470 --> 00:07:12.723
A guy like you would be used
to making evidence go away.

127
00:07:16.644 --> 00:07:18.104
Prove it.

128
00:07:19.772 --> 00:07:21.399
Look at the time.

129
00:07:21.482 --> 00:07:23.693
Wow. Surely we're almost done?

130
00:07:23.776 --> 00:07:25.111
That's true.

131
00:07:25.194 --> 00:07:26.612
One minute left.

132
00:07:30.158 --> 00:07:31.451
[Kenji sighs]

133
00:07:31.534 --> 00:07:32.952
[Mori] Okamoto…

134
00:07:33.995 --> 00:07:37.248
I knew an Okamoto once.
You must be his son.

135
00:07:44.589 --> 00:07:48.468
The two of us. we go way back.
your old man and I.

136
00:07:49.594 --> 00:07:51.846
He was just like you.

137
00:07:52.597 --> 00:07:54.932
Couldn't. or wouldn't. play the game.

138
00:07:55.016 --> 00:07:56.225
[laughs]

139
00:07:56.309 --> 00:07:59.145
No. he wasn't so smart in the end.

140
00:07:59.228 --> 00:08:01.397
Such a tragedy.

141
00:08:02.899 --> 00:08:03.900
[Mori croaks]

142
00:08:05.693 --> 00:08:06.944
You son of a bitch!

143
00:08:07.028 --> 00:08:08.529
- [attorney] Get off him!
- Let's go!

144
00:08:08.613 --> 00:08:09.655
We got him! Hold on!

145
00:08:09.739 --> 00:08:11.240
- What are you doing?
- You fucker!

146
00:08:11.324 --> 00:08:13.201
- Let go! Back off. now!
- You fucking shit!

147
00:08:13.284 --> 00:08:15.036
Hey! Hey! Let go!

148
00:08:15.119 --> 00:08:16.746
- [Kenji] Let go!
- [detective] Stop!

149
00:08:16.829 --> 00:08:19.040
- Fuck! You shithead!
- [detective] Calm down!

150
00:08:19.123 --> 00:08:21.542
- [Kenji grunts]
- Get a hold of yourself!

151
00:08:23.377 --> 00:08:24.795
Time's up.

152
00:08:25.296 --> 00:08:26.339
[laughs]

153
00:08:29.258 --> 00:08:31.302
[breathing heavily]

154
00:08:33.971 --> 00:08:35.264
Walk it off.

155
00:08:36.974 --> 00:08:38.643
You did the best you could.

156
00:08:39.769 --> 00:08:42.021
[Kyoko] Ugh. you're so heavy.
Almost there.

157
00:08:42.104 --> 00:08:43.606
- [Kenji] I'm fine.
- [Kyoko groans]

158
00:08:43.689 --> 00:08:45.483
[Kenji] Get off me. I said I'm fine.

159
00:08:45.983 --> 00:08:47.485
[Kyoko grunts. sighs]

160
00:08:47.568 --> 00:08:48.569
[Kenji groans]

161
00:08:50.363 --> 00:08:52.657
- [Kyoko] Damn.
- [Kenji groans]

162
00:08:52.740 --> 00:08:55.076
- [Kyoko] You gonna be okay?
- [Kenji groans]

163
00:08:57.161 --> 00:08:58.287
[Kyoko sighs]

164
00:08:58.371 --> 00:08:59.789
- Sorry.
- What?

165
00:08:59.872 --> 00:09:02.333
- [Kenji groans]
- Hey! Be careful!

166
00:09:04.210 --> 00:09:05.169
- Oh!
- [Kenji grunts]

167
00:09:05.253 --> 00:09:06.420
[Kyoko] Okay.

168
00:09:07.046 --> 00:09:08.881
- [soft music playing]
- [both groan]

169
00:09:08.965 --> 00:09:10.049
[Kenji sighs]

170
00:09:13.970 --> 00:09:16.597
- That son of a bitch.
- [Kyoko] Who?

171
00:09:17.598 --> 00:09:20.309
Bastard's never gonna face the music.

172
00:09:22.937 --> 00:09:27.483
He's just gonna do it again and again.
and he'll keep getting away with it.

173
00:09:28.276 --> 00:09:30.987
He's gonna learn from this time
and get smarter…

174
00:09:33.864 --> 00:09:38.369
There's no damn justice in the world.
A guy like him gets to go free?

175
00:09:40.538 --> 00:09:42.373
Why. son of a bitch.

176
00:09:43.791 --> 00:09:46.127
[soft music continues]

177
00:09:50.548 --> 00:09:52.550
[sighs softly]

178
00:09:55.177 --> 00:09:58.347
[server 1] Excuse me. sir. Do you know
if your guest is still on her way

179
00:09:58.431 --> 00:09:59.640
or when she'll be here?

180
00:10:00.141 --> 00:10:01.517
Yeah. sorry.

181
00:10:02.226 --> 00:10:04.437
Pretty sure she'll be here real soon.

182
00:10:04.979 --> 00:10:06.397
Thank you very much. sir.

183
00:10:09.900 --> 00:10:12.486
- [server 2] Right this way. please.
- [Kenji sighs]

184
00:10:14.030 --> 00:10:16.490
- [man] Nice place.
- [woman] Yeah. it's gorgeous.

185
00:10:21.495 --> 00:10:25.791
KYOKO KONO
ARE YOU OKAY. KYOKO?

186
00:10:25.875 --> 00:10:27.960
MICHIKO ABE

187
00:10:28.044 --> 00:10:29.629
- [phone vibrating]
- [sighs]

188
00:10:32.381 --> 00:10:34.342
- Yeah. what is it?
- [Michiko] <i>Bad news.</i>

189
00:10:35.343 --> 00:10:37.094
<i>I'm sending you the video now.</i>

190
00:10:43.851 --> 00:10:45.978
<i>JNT has obtained information</i>

191
00:10:46.062 --> 00:10:50.608
<i>revealing that Bit-Money-Trade's CEO.</i>
<i>Yasutoshi Mori. is under investigation</i>

192
00:10:50.691 --> 00:10:54.028
<i>in connection to the death</i>
<i>of a 17-year-old high-school girl.</i>

193
00:10:54.737 --> 00:10:58.032
<i>We now go to our investigative team's</i>
<i>interview with him.</i>

194
00:10:58.991 --> 00:11:01.035
<i>Excuse me! Excuse me. Yasutoshi Mori?</i>

195
00:11:01.535 --> 00:11:02.745
<i>Who the hell are you?</i>

196
00:11:02.828 --> 00:11:05.331
<i>- My name is Kyoko. I'm with JNT.</i>
- [tense music playing]

197
00:11:05.414 --> 00:11:07.166
<i>You were recently questioned by police</i>

198
00:11:07.249 --> 00:11:09.377
<i>about a schoolgirl</i>
<i>who died of an overdose.</i>

199
00:11:09.460 --> 00:11:10.503
<i>Care to comment?</i>

200
00:11:10.586 --> 00:11:14.131
{\an8}<i>- Get that camera out of my face.</i>
<i>- I see some of your shareholders are here.</i>

201
00:11:14.215 --> 00:11:16.425
{\an8}<i>Anything you'd like to say</i>
<i>to put their minds at ease?</i>

202
00:11:16.509 --> 00:11:18.052
{\an8}<i>Nah. I'm clean.</i>

203
00:11:18.135 --> 00:11:19.387
{\an8}<i>If you have nothing to hide.</i>

204
00:11:19.470 --> 00:11:22.390
{\an8}<i>why did you refuse to give investigators</i>
<i>access to your phone?</i>

205
00:11:22.473 --> 00:11:24.350
{\an8}<i>Get out of here before I call someone.</i>

206
00:11:24.433 --> 00:11:25.309
{\an8}<i>Hey!</i>

207
00:11:26.018 --> 00:11:29.230
{\an8}<i>- Can we get her out of here?</i>
<i>- Nice phone. Mr. Mori. Is it new?</i>

208
00:11:29.730 --> 00:11:33.109
{\an8}<i>You got rid of your old phone. didn't you.</i>
<i>so they couldn't see what was in there?</i>

209
00:11:33.192 --> 00:11:36.445
{\an8}<i>- The girl asked you for help. didn't she?</i>
- [guard] <i>No. you're leaving.</i>

210
00:11:36.529 --> 00:11:39.949
{\an8}[Kyoko] <i>What did you do to her? Hey!</i>
<i>The people deserve to know the truth!</i>

211
00:11:40.032 --> 00:11:42.827
[newscaster] <i>Mr. Mori admitted</i>
<i>to having been questioned</i>

212
00:11:42.910 --> 00:11:44.995
<i>but left without further comment.</i>

213
00:11:45.079 --> 00:11:46.997
<i>- He later denied…</i>
<i>- ♪ Happy birthday to you ♪</i>

214
00:11:47.081 --> 00:11:50.167
♪ <i>Happy birthday to you </i>♪

215
00:11:50.251 --> 00:11:51.877
♪ <i>Happy birthday… </i>♪

216
00:11:53.337 --> 00:11:55.089
[chief] A certain journalist has reported…

217
00:11:55.172 --> 00:11:56.424
MORI COMMITS SUICIDE

218
00:11:56.507 --> 00:11:59.343
…about an active investigation
you were in charge of.

219
00:11:59.427 --> 00:12:01.429
[chilling music playing]

220
00:12:03.305 --> 00:12:05.141
We need you outta here today.

221
00:12:05.224 --> 00:12:06.559
You're suspended.

222
00:12:11.355 --> 00:12:13.357
[Kyoko] I have nothing more to say.

223
00:12:13.441 --> 00:12:15.609
[Michiko] All right.
I got a good read on you.

224
00:12:15.693 --> 00:12:18.696
You're the kind of person
who'll do anything for the story.

225
00:12:19.321 --> 00:12:21.115
- Aren't you. Ms. Kono?
- [detective] Abe.

226
00:12:21.657 --> 00:12:22.742
That's enough.

227
00:12:24.577 --> 00:12:25.578
Ah. there you go.

228
00:12:25.661 --> 00:12:28.706
We took a look at your phone.
There's nothing out of the ordinary.

229
00:12:29.206 --> 00:12:30.499
Apologies.

230
00:12:31.459 --> 00:12:33.919
You're free to go for today. Ms. Kono.

231
00:12:35.713 --> 00:12:37.423
Thanks. If you'll excuse me.

232
00:12:44.096 --> 00:12:44.972
Kyoko.

233
00:12:47.641 --> 00:12:48.934
Kenji.

234
00:12:50.811 --> 00:12:52.062
You saw all that?

235
00:12:55.024 --> 00:12:55.900
Yeah.

236
00:12:57.818 --> 00:12:59.361
[Kenji sighs]

237
00:13:00.821 --> 00:13:05.242
It would be best if you took a step back
from this case. all right?

238
00:13:07.453 --> 00:13:09.497
We've got it under control.

239
00:13:13.793 --> 00:13:16.003
Go chase down some other story.

240
00:13:16.086 --> 00:13:17.755
Stop getting in our way.

241
00:13:18.756 --> 00:13:22.301
What do you mean?
When did I get in your way?

242
00:13:22.885 --> 00:13:26.180
Oh. I don't know. was it when you stole
evidence to run down a lead?

243
00:13:28.599 --> 00:13:31.143
You thought you knew better than we did.

244
00:13:31.894 --> 00:13:33.896
And because of you. Mori's dead.

245
00:13:33.979 --> 00:13:37.566
Because of you. we'll never know
the whole truth about what he did.

246
00:13:37.650 --> 00:13:40.486
Committing suicide
is basically an admission of his guilt.

247
00:13:40.986 --> 00:13:43.489
He killed that girl.
He deserved what he got.

248
00:13:43.572 --> 00:13:45.866
[somber acoustic guitar music playing]

249
00:13:54.166 --> 00:13:55.793
[Kenji sighs]

250
00:14:08.514 --> 00:14:10.558
[woman] Bear with me. This is unusual.

251
00:14:10.641 --> 00:14:14.228
DNA analysis requires biological material.
like blood or sweat.

252
00:14:14.311 --> 00:14:16.897
that can normally be pulled
from a suspect's clothing.

253
00:14:16.981 --> 00:14:18.440
But in this case…

254
00:14:18.524 --> 00:14:19.817
What'd you find?

255
00:14:20.860 --> 00:14:23.279
Well. that's just it.
We didn't find any samples.

256
00:14:23.362 --> 00:14:24.822
[tense music playing]

257
00:14:24.905 --> 00:14:27.116
[sighs] It's a first for me.

258
00:14:27.616 --> 00:14:29.326
It's like he doesn't even exist.

259
00:14:30.786 --> 00:14:32.288
[chief sighs]

260
00:14:32.371 --> 00:14:33.914
Anything on his identity yet?

261
00:14:33.998 --> 00:14:37.418
We tried running his face
through recognition software. but no hits.

262
00:14:37.918 --> 00:14:39.211
We'll widen the search.

263
00:14:39.295 --> 00:14:41.589
[sighs] Son of a bitch.

264
00:14:41.672 --> 00:14:43.257
It's a shit show.

265
00:14:44.633 --> 00:14:48.721
What about the. uh. White Center
or whatever it was called? Anything there?

266
00:14:48.804 --> 00:14:52.558
Looks like it was operating
in Yamanashi Prefecture 30 years ago.

267
00:14:53.058 --> 00:14:57.313
Although there's hardly any record of it.
so it'll take some time to learn more.

268
00:14:57.938 --> 00:15:00.232
- [chief] What? You see something?
- Uh. no.

269
00:15:00.774 --> 00:15:04.069
It's just that the stitching is different
on this button.

270
00:15:04.153 --> 00:15:07.948
- [chief] Stitching?
- [Kenji] As if it were added on later.

271
00:15:09.867 --> 00:15:11.076
[chief] What's that?

272
00:15:11.160 --> 00:15:13.037
[Michiko] There's a pattern
on the underside.

273
00:15:13.120 --> 00:15:15.456
WHITE CENTER. KYUGO SANO. CONNECTION
NO RESULTS

274
00:15:15.998 --> 00:15:18.375
- [Kyoko] Anything on White Center?
- Uh. no.

275
00:15:18.459 --> 00:15:20.502
There's nothing about it anywhere.

276
00:15:20.586 --> 00:15:23.380
Even if it was destroyed.
there should still be some record.

277
00:15:27.551 --> 00:15:30.346
Which means there's a chance
those records were scrubbed.

278
00:15:30.429 --> 00:15:32.431
[Tatsuya] Uh. excuse me. Ms. Kono?

279
00:15:33.015 --> 00:15:35.309
- Do you have a second?
- Mm.

280
00:15:36.852 --> 00:15:39.897
I've got something here that I think
you're gonna want to check out.

281
00:15:39.980 --> 00:15:44.610
It looks like this White Center was
a social welfare facility 27 years ago.

282
00:15:45.945 --> 00:15:47.696
Uh. it was in Yamanashi Prefecture.

283
00:15:47.780 --> 00:15:51.408
Its mission statement seems to do
with supporting the social reintegration

284
00:15:51.492 --> 00:15:53.327
of orphans and homeless people.

285
00:15:53.410 --> 00:15:56.372
And I think I can find
the connection to Professor Sano

286
00:15:56.455 --> 00:15:58.457
if I dig a bit deeper into all of this.

287
00:15:59.124 --> 00:16:02.586
Whoa. Great work. Tatsuya.
Where did you find all this info?

288
00:16:02.670 --> 00:16:05.965
Uh. right after the Human Vapor's
first message went out.

289
00:16:06.048 --> 00:16:07.633
someone got in touch.

290
00:16:07.716 --> 00:16:10.552
- Someone?
- [Tatsuya] Yeah. uh…

291
00:16:11.178 --> 00:16:14.098
A retired newspaper reporter said
he had written an article

292
00:16:14.181 --> 00:16:15.849
about White Center years ago.

293
00:16:16.850 --> 00:16:19.603
- Can you set up a meeting?
- Yeah. sure.

294
00:16:23.023 --> 00:16:26.402
[man] Get your hands off me!
I didn't do anything. I swear!

295
00:16:32.324 --> 00:16:36.328
- [Michiko] We got a hit on the symbol.
- [Kenji] The Fujishiro Syndicate.

296
00:16:36.412 --> 00:16:39.456
- They're linked to the Kasuga Group?
- [Michiko] That's right.

297
00:16:39.540 --> 00:16:42.459
And we got confirmation
that it's the Fujishiro crest.

298
00:16:44.169 --> 00:16:47.673
How's the Human Vapor connected
to a yakuza syndicate?

299
00:16:48.841 --> 00:16:52.970
- What do we know about the Fujishiro?
- That's where all this gets interesting.

300
00:16:53.053 --> 00:16:55.681
Recently. they've been
expanding their operations.

301
00:16:56.223 --> 00:16:59.143
There might be a new player
in the syndicate or behind the scenes.

302
00:17:03.355 --> 00:17:04.732
It's one button.

303
00:17:05.232 --> 00:17:08.068
Let's say the Human Vapor
used to be a member of the Syndicate.

304
00:17:08.569 --> 00:17:10.279
why wouldn't he rep the group more?

305
00:17:10.362 --> 00:17:13.824
Why only wear one button?
That's weird. don't you think?

306
00:17:44.855 --> 00:17:47.483
[Kenji] This pocket square.
how it's folded…

307
00:17:47.566 --> 00:17:49.568
I swear I've seen it before.

308
00:17:55.240 --> 00:17:56.784
[Michiko] The pocket square?

309
00:18:03.624 --> 00:18:05.793
[Michiko] Professor Sano had the same one.

310
00:18:06.376 --> 00:18:07.377
[Kenji] Exactly.

311
00:18:09.004 --> 00:18:11.965
He might be leaving us clues
as to his next target.

312
00:18:12.674 --> 00:18:16.261
[Michiko] It increases the risk
of getting caught. Why would he do that?

313
00:18:17.513 --> 00:18:19.389
[indistinct chattering]

314
00:18:20.974 --> 00:18:23.227
[light. intriguing music playing]

315
00:18:24.186 --> 00:18:26.313
- [server 1] Hi there.
- [server 2] This way. sir.

316
00:18:27.481 --> 00:18:29.983
[server 1] Anywhere you'd like.
We'll be right with you.

317
00:18:30.484 --> 00:18:31.693
- Thanks.
- [Kyoko] Ah!

318
00:18:32.694 --> 00:18:36.240
Shinichi Kato? You're the reporter
who contacted us with the information?

319
00:18:36.323 --> 00:18:39.576
[chuckles] I'm not sure
you should be calling me a reporter.

320
00:18:39.660 --> 00:18:41.578
I've been retired for a while.

321
00:18:42.079 --> 00:18:43.622
I'm Kyoko Kono from JNT.

322
00:18:44.123 --> 00:18:45.541
- And this is…
- [Tatsuya] Ah…

323
00:18:46.041 --> 00:18:47.626
Tatsuya Nishiyama.

324
00:18:49.378 --> 00:18:52.256
[sighs] I'll cut right to the chase.

325
00:18:52.756 --> 00:18:56.176
We understand you wrote about
the White Center when it was established?

326
00:18:56.260 --> 00:18:57.386
I did.

327
00:18:58.220 --> 00:19:00.556
Yes. I believe it was ten articles in all.

328
00:19:00.639 --> 00:19:01.849
That's interesting.

329
00:19:01.932 --> 00:19:05.727
We've been looking for any information.
and nothing's come up.

330
00:19:10.440 --> 00:19:12.818
- [server 3] What can I get you?
- A cup of coffee.

331
00:19:12.901 --> 00:19:15.154
- [server 3] All right.
- Uh. cream soda.

332
00:19:15.237 --> 00:19:16.363
[server 3] No problem.

333
00:19:19.199 --> 00:19:22.286
There was something happening
in Yamanashi at the time.

334
00:19:23.745 --> 00:19:26.123
The Children of the World Peace Expo.

335
00:19:26.623 --> 00:19:28.584
Oh. I remember that.

336
00:19:29.334 --> 00:19:30.210
[Tatsuya] Uh…

337
00:19:30.794 --> 00:19:34.047
I'm not surprised young people today
wouldn't know. but back in '99.

338
00:19:34.131 --> 00:19:37.843
hosting an international event like that
was all anyone could talk about.

339
00:19:37.926 --> 00:19:39.219
4-HOUR WAIT AT ENTRANCE GATE

340
00:19:39.303 --> 00:19:40.804
But that same year…

341
00:19:47.102 --> 00:19:49.104
a meteorite fell in Yamanashi.

342
00:19:49.188 --> 00:19:51.064
Obviously not a common occurrence.

343
00:19:51.565 --> 00:19:53.817
- Plus it started a forest fire.
- [foreboding music playing]

344
00:19:53.901 --> 00:19:55.944
A meteorite? Really?

345
00:19:56.653 --> 00:19:58.697
Was it big news then. or no?

346
00:19:59.531 --> 00:20:02.284
People were more excited
about the Peace Expo.

347
00:20:02.784 --> 00:20:05.996
which would explain
why it didn't get quite as much coverage.

348
00:20:09.208 --> 00:20:12.544
Professor Sano was head of the Meteorite
Safety Committee at the time.

349
00:20:12.628 --> 00:20:14.755
PROFESSOR SANO
NO HARMFUL EFFECTS FROM METEORITE

350
00:20:14.838 --> 00:20:19.092
He said the debris was completely safe.
didn't pose any threat.

351
00:20:19.176 --> 00:20:20.886
and the public was lied to.

352
00:20:21.845 --> 00:20:23.013
It wasn't true?

353
00:20:23.513 --> 00:20:26.225
[Shinichi] No.
Harmful substances had been found.

354
00:20:26.308 --> 00:20:28.936
What he did was a cover-up.
pure and simple.

355
00:20:32.773 --> 00:20:36.401
{\an8}NO HARMFUL EFFECTS SEEN FROM METEORITE

356
00:20:36.485 --> 00:20:39.363
Cleanup was being taken care of quietly.

357
00:20:39.947 --> 00:20:43.367
By a certain facility.
privately owned and operated.

358
00:20:46.161 --> 00:20:48.080
You understand what I'm saying?

359
00:20:49.331 --> 00:20:51.208
White Center. you mean?

360
00:20:52.167 --> 00:20:53.293
[Shinichi] Exactly.

361
00:21:00.926 --> 00:21:03.220
White Center
was said to be for social welfare.

362
00:21:04.680 --> 00:21:06.515
But that was just a cover.

363
00:21:07.724 --> 00:21:11.019
In reality. they used the residents
for all kinds of manual labor

364
00:21:11.103 --> 00:21:12.896
that needed to be kept quiet.

365
00:21:19.194 --> 00:21:21.446
I investigated the Center
and its management.

366
00:21:21.530 --> 00:21:23.282
but when I went to publish…

367
00:21:23.365 --> 00:21:25.075
All your articles were rejected.

368
00:21:25.158 --> 00:21:28.495
in favor of…
the Children of the World Peace Expo.

369
00:21:28.996 --> 00:21:32.249
All the government wanted was
some positive international attention

370
00:21:32.332 --> 00:21:34.001
after the decade we'd had.

371
00:21:34.501 --> 00:21:37.087
And the meteorite.
White Center. the cover-up.

372
00:21:37.587 --> 00:21:40.674
it didn't look good.
That's the way the world works.

373
00:21:40.757 --> 00:21:43.218
[Kyoko] Who's this?
He's not named in the caption.

374
00:21:43.302 --> 00:21:44.970
Did he work for the White Center?

375
00:21:45.512 --> 00:21:48.557
[Shinichi] Oh yes. that's Obata.
He was the director at the time.

376
00:21:49.516 --> 00:21:51.768
Do you know
how to get in touch with him now?

377
00:21:55.605 --> 00:21:58.984
[Shinichi] After the peace expo.
he disappeared without a trace.

378
00:22:00.444 --> 00:22:01.862
Like a ghost.

379
00:22:05.490 --> 00:22:07.951
Sorry to keep you waiting.
Here's your coffee.

380
00:22:08.035 --> 00:22:09.161
[music fades out]

381
00:22:09.244 --> 00:22:11.288
- Do you need any milk?
- No. thanks. I'm fine.

382
00:22:11.788 --> 00:22:13.123
And your cream soda.

383
00:22:20.339 --> 00:22:22.758
[Shinichi] Not so long
after he disappeared.

384
00:22:23.383 --> 00:22:24.926
I saw him again.

385
00:22:26.136 --> 00:22:27.346
You saw him?

386
00:22:28.930 --> 00:22:32.184
I was looking for a place to eat
while I was on the road.

387
00:22:33.310 --> 00:22:38.190
There were… volunteers distributing bags
of food to hungry children.

388
00:22:38.273 --> 00:22:41.443
And you saw Obata with them.
you're saying? He was volunteering?

389
00:22:46.448 --> 00:22:48.784
I called out to him to get his attention.

390
00:22:49.451 --> 00:22:51.787
but he ignored me. They all did.

391
00:22:53.372 --> 00:22:55.040
[Shinichi inhales slowly]

392
00:22:55.123 --> 00:22:58.919
They were all calling him
by a different name. It wasn't Obata.

393
00:23:00.295 --> 00:23:01.546
What was it?

394
00:23:02.672 --> 00:23:04.966
It was quite similar. I recall.

395
00:23:06.760 --> 00:23:08.720
It's gone. Darn.

396
00:23:10.430 --> 00:23:11.807
Where'd you see him last?

397
00:23:12.891 --> 00:23:14.684
What do you think this is. a handout?

398
00:23:20.690 --> 00:23:22.234
What's it worth to you?

399
00:23:31.159 --> 00:23:32.494
[bolt creaking open]

400
00:23:33.286 --> 00:23:34.746
[bolt clattering]

401
00:23:36.957 --> 00:23:37.999
[gates clanging]

402
00:23:39.167 --> 00:23:41.378
[gates screeching open]

403
00:23:41.461 --> 00:23:43.463
[haunting music droning]

404
00:23:51.304 --> 00:23:53.640
What happened? Where is everyone?

405
00:24:00.397 --> 00:24:02.149
[zipper opening]

406
00:24:15.036 --> 00:24:16.037
[gasps]

407
00:24:21.209 --> 00:24:22.377
[inhales sharply]

408
00:24:22.461 --> 00:24:24.254
[music fades]

409
00:24:24.337 --> 00:24:26.339
[waves lapping gently]

410
00:24:39.895 --> 00:24:42.063
[cries softly]

411
00:24:44.816 --> 00:24:45.817
[groaning]

412
00:24:49.988 --> 00:24:51.990
[melancholy music playing]

413
00:24:52.532 --> 00:24:53.700
[groaning]

414
00:24:58.580 --> 00:25:00.540
[sniffling and groaning]

415
00:25:03.251 --> 00:25:05.253
[crying]

416
00:25:08.131 --> 00:25:10.759
[anguished groaning]

417
00:25:16.890 --> 00:25:18.141
[Kyoko] <i>Hiroki Obata.</i>

418
00:25:18.225 --> 00:25:20.352
He was the director of White Center.

419
00:25:20.852 --> 00:25:24.523
These days. we think he's volunteering
with youth groups in Shizuoka.

420
00:25:26.399 --> 00:25:29.194
We're not sure where exactly.
but I'm going to find him.

421
00:25:29.736 --> 00:25:30.862
[director sighs]

422
00:25:32.155 --> 00:25:33.823
So this guy. Obata.

423
00:25:33.907 --> 00:25:36.868
do you think
you can get him to go on the record?

424
00:25:39.079 --> 00:25:42.541
He'd need to.
You're sure you can get him to talk?

425
00:25:43.124 --> 00:25:46.002
- I'll do my best.
- Your best isn't good enough. Kono.

426
00:25:46.545 --> 00:25:50.298
This peace expo was a major event.
No one wants to tarnish its memory.

427
00:25:50.382 --> 00:25:52.175
You'll make enemies left and right.

428
00:25:52.259 --> 00:25:53.885
I understand that. sir.

429
00:25:57.264 --> 00:25:58.765
And you're prepared for that?

430
00:26:00.100 --> 00:26:00.976
Yes.

431
00:26:01.476 --> 00:26:02.602
This is the story.

432
00:26:03.144 --> 00:26:04.479
I can feel it in my gut.

433
00:26:12.821 --> 00:26:13.822
Better get going.

434
00:26:13.905 --> 00:26:19.160
FUJISHIRO ENTERPRISES

435
00:26:20.453 --> 00:26:22.455
[suspenseful music playing]

436
00:26:27.460 --> 00:26:30.922
[Michiko] You think the Human Vapor
is going to kill a member of the yakuza?

437
00:26:32.090 --> 00:26:33.717
You can't be serious.

438
00:26:34.676 --> 00:26:37.304
Look. the button
could be some kind of hint.

439
00:26:38.930 --> 00:26:40.932
Maybe he'll show up. You never know.

440
00:26:41.016 --> 00:26:42.142
[Palm] Give me my tray!

441
00:26:42.225 --> 00:26:44.853
- [man 1] Get out of here.
- [Palm] I'm sorry. I just…

442
00:26:44.936 --> 00:26:46.021
I'm missing one.

443
00:26:46.104 --> 00:26:48.064
- [man 1] Aw. gonna cry?
- [Palm] I need it.

444
00:26:48.148 --> 00:26:49.482
[man 2] Hey! Get out of here.

445
00:26:49.983 --> 00:26:52.569
- You need a shave. You look like shit.
- I need my tray.

446
00:26:52.652 --> 00:26:55.280
- My boss will be so mad.
- Do I look like I care?

447
00:26:55.363 --> 00:26:57.324
- Get the fuck out of here.
- I need my tray--

448
00:26:57.407 --> 00:26:58.867
[motorbikes approaching]

449
00:27:01.369 --> 00:27:05.165
- [Kenji] Abe. get some shots of this.
- [tense music playing]

450
00:27:05.248 --> 00:27:07.083
- [man 3] What's up?
- [camera clicking]

451
00:27:07.167 --> 00:27:09.628
- [man 1] Let's go.
- [Palm] Hang on. I need my tray!

452
00:27:09.711 --> 00:27:12.005
- [man 3] Hey. food boy!
- [Palm] I want it back.

453
00:27:12.088 --> 00:27:14.257
[man 3] Trying to start some shit?
I'll kill you!

454
00:27:14.341 --> 00:27:15.675
- [man 1] Yo!
- [man 3] Chill out.

455
00:27:18.428 --> 00:27:20.430
[camera clicking]

456
00:27:26.811 --> 00:27:28.271
Palm! Hey. Palm!

457
00:27:31.316 --> 00:27:32.525
Palm. wait up!

458
00:27:33.568 --> 00:27:34.903
You remember me?

459
00:27:36.738 --> 00:27:39.074
- Yeah. you're that police officer.
- Uh-huh.

460
00:27:40.200 --> 00:27:42.952
That's me.
and right now. I'm on the clock.

461
00:27:43.036 --> 00:27:45.205
I'm investigating some bad guys.
you understand?

462
00:27:45.288 --> 00:27:48.291
Maybe you could tell me…
what it was like in there.

463
00:27:49.834 --> 00:27:51.086
It was bad. yeah?

464
00:27:52.045 --> 00:27:53.755
They were going on about the news.

465
00:27:53.838 --> 00:27:56.174
They were talking about the Human Vapor.

466
00:27:57.300 --> 00:27:58.927
Said it was an emergency.

467
00:28:01.054 --> 00:28:02.889
And those guys that just went in.

468
00:28:02.972 --> 00:28:05.642
they looked like they came
from somewhere else. Hear anything?

469
00:28:05.725 --> 00:28:07.268
They were scary dudes

470
00:28:07.352 --> 00:28:08.770
and really dangerous.

471
00:28:09.270 --> 00:28:11.147
They might've had guns. I'm not sure.

472
00:28:12.691 --> 00:28:14.442
Thanks a lot. You did good.

473
00:28:14.943 --> 00:28:15.985
[Palm] No problem.

474
00:28:16.986 --> 00:28:18.488
- Oh. right.
- [Kenji] Hmm?

475
00:28:20.198 --> 00:28:21.574
I wanted to say thanks.

476
00:28:21.658 --> 00:28:22.492
Hmm?

477
00:28:23.034 --> 00:28:26.371
[Palm] Because of you. I quit that place.
I deliver for these guys now.

478
00:28:26.454 --> 00:28:28.123
Check it out. Isn't it awesome?

479
00:28:28.206 --> 00:28:30.083
- Ah!
- What do you think?

480
00:28:30.750 --> 00:28:31.960
It suits me. right?

481
00:28:32.043 --> 00:28:33.128
It does. yeah.

482
00:28:34.421 --> 00:28:36.965
I appreciate what you did.
I know my worth.

483
00:28:37.507 --> 00:28:38.925
I won't assume any less.

484
00:28:40.051 --> 00:28:40.885
Uh-huh.

485
00:28:41.386 --> 00:28:43.763
Oh! [chuckles]

486
00:28:43.847 --> 00:28:44.848
Sure.

487
00:28:47.308 --> 00:28:48.226
Hmm.

488
00:28:50.061 --> 00:28:51.730
What's the opposite of a dead end?

489
00:28:51.813 --> 00:28:55.233
We found 32 volunteer youth groups
in Shizuoka alone.

490
00:28:56.568 --> 00:28:59.446
[Tatsuya] If any individual group
receives government funding.

491
00:28:59.529 --> 00:29:02.282
then we can request
information about their staff.

492
00:29:02.782 --> 00:29:06.870
but if they're a private group. privacy
laws make it a lot harder to get anything.

493
00:29:06.953 --> 00:29:10.373
Of course. Well. it doesn't have to be
through official channels.

494
00:29:10.457 --> 00:29:13.835
Maybe we can scrub their websites
or social media for photos?

495
00:29:14.377 --> 00:29:15.503
[Tatsuya] Hmm…

496
00:29:20.383 --> 00:29:21.843
Wait. hang on! That photo.

497
00:29:24.012 --> 00:29:26.139
- Put it up on the screen?
- Yeah.

498
00:29:30.894 --> 00:29:33.438
So? It could be the same guy.

499
00:29:33.938 --> 00:29:35.940
[determined music playing]

500
00:29:37.108 --> 00:29:40.487
[Tatsuya] Hat. glasses. beard…

501
00:29:40.570 --> 00:29:42.864
- The mole. too.
- What's this man's name?

502
00:29:42.947 --> 00:29:44.866
[man] Uh. hang on. I'm sure it's here.

503
00:29:45.366 --> 00:29:46.409
{\an8}It's… Ah!

504
00:29:46.493 --> 00:29:48.995
{\an8}Hiroshi Ozaki. He's the director.

505
00:29:50.413 --> 00:29:52.874
Right. What did Kato say about it?

506
00:29:52.957 --> 00:29:55.960
That Obata's alias sounded a lot
like his real name.

507
00:29:57.462 --> 00:29:59.214
Hiroki and Hiroshi…

508
00:29:59.756 --> 00:30:01.299
Ozaki and Obata…

509
00:30:02.675 --> 00:30:05.178
- You all see it too?
- Can't be a coincidence.

510
00:30:06.471 --> 00:30:09.808
Even if it is him. he's not gonna want
to admit to being connected.

511
00:30:09.891 --> 00:30:13.186
Hmm. Though. if it is Obata. he…

512
00:30:14.312 --> 00:30:17.857
he must know the kind of danger he's in
from the Human Vapor.

513
00:30:19.692 --> 00:30:23.780
But if we're too forceful.
he could go on the run again.

514
00:30:25.156 --> 00:30:27.784
Hey. Ozaki's listed on the website.

515
00:30:28.409 --> 00:30:30.286
- [man 1] Time to eat!
- [woman] Dinner time!

516
00:30:30.370 --> 00:30:32.372
[man 1] Oh. look. Mm-mm!

517
00:30:33.790 --> 00:30:37.001
- [man 1] Hello. One for Leo too. please.
- [woman] Coming right up.

518
00:30:38.586 --> 00:30:41.548
Hello. Kazuha. Have you seen Shota?

519
00:30:43.424 --> 00:30:45.844
- [Kazuha] Mm-mm.
- [Obata] Oh.

520
00:30:47.345 --> 00:30:49.931
- [phone vibrating]
- [woman] All right. here you go!

521
00:30:54.978 --> 00:30:57.438
- Here. It's Kazuha's.
- Okay. Thank you. sir.

522
00:30:57.522 --> 00:30:58.731
[phone vibrating]

523
00:31:00.859 --> 00:31:01.734
Hello?

524
00:31:02.235 --> 00:31:04.863
[Kyoko] <i>Hello.</i>
<i>I'm looking to speak with Hiroshi Ozaki.</i>

525
00:31:05.738 --> 00:31:06.865
This is he.

526
00:31:07.365 --> 00:31:09.951
<i>I'm sorry to call you</i>
<i>out of the blue like this. Mr. Ozaki.</i>

527
00:31:10.034 --> 00:31:12.745
<i>My name is Kyoko Kono.</i>
<i>I'm a journalist with JNT.</i>

528
00:31:14.873 --> 00:31:17.125
I was the one interviewing Professor Sano

529
00:31:17.208 --> 00:31:19.127
<i>when he was killed by the Human Vapor.</i>

530
00:31:19.210 --> 00:31:21.212
[suspenseful music playing]

531
00:31:21.796 --> 00:31:24.757
Oh. I see.
What can I do for you. Ms. Kono?

532
00:31:26.259 --> 00:31:27.927
I wanted to talk about your past.

533
00:31:28.761 --> 00:31:31.139
<i>You used to be the director</i>
<i>of White Center.</i>

534
00:31:33.725 --> 00:31:35.393
[Obata exhales slowly]

535
00:31:36.102 --> 00:31:37.395
I'm sorry.

536
00:31:37.979 --> 00:31:40.189
You must have the wrong number.

537
00:31:40.273 --> 00:31:43.443
Just a minute. please.
You haven't been living under a rock.

538
00:31:44.152 --> 00:31:47.280
I hope you're aware the Human Vapor said
he was gonna kill again.

539
00:31:47.822 --> 00:31:50.742
He might set his sights on you
because of your link to the center.

540
00:31:50.825 --> 00:31:52.827
[tense music playing]

541
00:31:55.622 --> 00:31:57.290
[Obata] <i>I'm sorry. Wrong number.</i>

542
00:31:57.790 --> 00:31:59.334
<i>- Goodbye.</i>
- [call disconnects]

543
00:32:00.418 --> 00:32:01.544
[sighs]

544
00:32:04.964 --> 00:32:06.341
Well. that's that then.

545
00:32:07.216 --> 00:32:08.551
It's definitely him.

546
00:32:13.097 --> 00:32:14.223
[man] Mr. Ozaki.

547
00:32:14.307 --> 00:32:16.768
- Sir? Sir? Mr. Ozaki!
- [music fades out]

548
00:32:16.851 --> 00:32:19.270
It's someone from Shota's school
on the phone. sir.

549
00:32:19.354 --> 00:32:21.981
He's in trouble.
It's something to do with stealing?

550
00:32:22.065 --> 00:32:23.358
Ow! Hey!

551
00:32:24.108 --> 00:32:26.486
We don't pinch. okay? What are you doing?

552
00:32:27.028 --> 00:32:27.904
At school?

553
00:32:29.197 --> 00:32:30.657
- Hello. sir.
- Hello.

554
00:32:33.618 --> 00:32:35.828
[brass and wind instruments playing]

555
00:32:35.912 --> 00:32:37.121
[Obata] It must be here.

556
00:32:39.165 --> 00:32:40.708
Excuse me. sorry. Excuse me.

557
00:32:43.753 --> 00:32:45.046
[teacher] Now. Shota…

558
00:32:47.256 --> 00:32:48.883
no one's mad at you. okay?

559
00:32:48.967 --> 00:32:50.927
We just want you to tell us the truth.

560
00:32:53.012 --> 00:32:54.597
I heard you saw Yoshitsune

561
00:32:55.223 --> 00:32:57.850
stealing money
from other students' wallets?

562
00:32:58.351 --> 00:32:59.477
Is that right?

563
00:33:02.105 --> 00:33:03.439
You can tell me.

564
00:33:11.698 --> 00:33:12.573
[sighs]

565
00:33:13.616 --> 00:33:16.327
Daisuke says
that you were with him at the time.

566
00:33:16.411 --> 00:33:18.746
that you both saw Yoshitsune stealing.

567
00:33:21.207 --> 00:33:22.208
Did you?

568
00:33:26.045 --> 00:33:27.130
Is it true?

569
00:33:44.731 --> 00:33:45.565
Yeah.

570
00:33:46.816 --> 00:33:48.067
Yeah. I saw it.

571
00:33:48.151 --> 00:33:49.986
[woman sighs with relief]

572
00:34:05.585 --> 00:34:07.128
[Shota sighs]

573
00:34:11.132 --> 00:34:12.550
Mr. Ozaki…

574
00:34:15.928 --> 00:34:16.971
I couldn't…

575
00:34:19.515 --> 00:34:21.934
I couldn't tell the truth. I'm sorry.

576
00:34:32.153 --> 00:34:33.321
<i>I lied to her.</i>

577
00:34:38.201 --> 00:34:39.619
Daisuke did it.

578
00:34:40.328 --> 00:34:41.454
[Obata sighs softly]

579
00:34:44.749 --> 00:34:46.250
He's the one who stole.

580
00:34:47.335 --> 00:34:49.545
And I saw it. I saw him do it.

581
00:34:57.303 --> 00:34:59.597
Why didn't you tell the teacher
what you saw?

582
00:35:01.516 --> 00:35:02.725
I just… I don't know.

583
00:35:03.226 --> 00:35:06.604
I was worried something bad would happen
if I told on him. I guess.

584
00:35:10.733 --> 00:35:13.986
Like with Yoshitsune.
He's gonna get bullied now.

585
00:35:14.487 --> 00:35:16.614
And I didn't want everyone picking on me.

586
00:35:23.329 --> 00:35:24.705
But now it's too late.

587
00:35:26.415 --> 00:35:27.750
It doesn't matter what I do.

588
00:35:27.834 --> 00:35:30.336
Even if I tell the truth.
nothing's gonna change.

589
00:35:37.093 --> 00:35:38.261
Daisuke…

590
00:35:38.970 --> 00:35:41.055
He's the most popular kid in school.

591
00:35:41.931 --> 00:35:43.391
He's class president.

592
00:35:45.059 --> 00:35:47.937
And. uh. Yoshitsune. he's…

593
00:35:48.521 --> 00:35:49.355
uh…

594
00:35:51.357 --> 00:35:52.358
not like that.

595
00:35:52.441 --> 00:35:56.154
He's always alone and doesn't have
a lot of friends. you know?

596
00:36:01.325 --> 00:36:03.035
So… Yeah.

597
00:36:03.119 --> 00:36:05.496
I guess that's it. It's just. like…

598
00:36:05.997 --> 00:36:11.669
basically. it doesn't really matter
what I do. it doesn't change anything. so…

599
00:36:15.840 --> 00:36:17.049
Shota.

600
00:36:17.550 --> 00:36:18.593
Yes. sir?

601
00:36:19.677 --> 00:36:21.804
You know the truth about something.

602
00:36:24.682 --> 00:36:26.642
If you choose to stay silent…

603
00:36:30.897 --> 00:36:33.482
it'll haunt you for the rest of your life.

604
00:36:33.566 --> 00:36:35.610
[poignant music playing]

605
00:36:37.987 --> 00:36:40.531
So please don't give up on the truth.

606
00:36:41.824 --> 00:36:43.659
For your own peace of mind.

607
00:36:51.334 --> 00:36:53.586
Words have power. and so does silence.

608
00:36:54.837 --> 00:36:56.255
If you do nothing…

609
00:36:58.758 --> 00:37:02.136
that makes you no better
than the kids bullying Yoshitsune.

610
00:37:05.723 --> 00:37:07.475
Is that really what you want?

611
00:37:17.735 --> 00:37:19.528
[Shota cries softly]

612
00:37:27.453 --> 00:37:28.579
No. it's not.

613
00:37:33.793 --> 00:37:36.712
[breathes deeply]

614
00:37:39.590 --> 00:37:40.549
[sighs]

615
00:37:47.014 --> 00:37:48.140
[Obata] Let's go home.

616
00:38:05.825 --> 00:38:07.994
[low. suspenseful music playing]

617
00:38:25.803 --> 00:38:28.014
[mysterious music playing]

618
00:38:41.902 --> 00:38:48.159
WHITE CENTER
WORK JOURNAL

619
00:38:48.743 --> 00:38:53.748
METEORITE CLEANUP OPERATION
JANUARY TO APRIL. 1999

620
00:38:59.253 --> 00:39:02.465
METEORITE IMPACT CONTAMINATION AREA

621
00:39:17.063 --> 00:39:18.898
Just skin and bones…

622
00:39:30.868 --> 00:39:35.039
MISSING

623
00:39:40.711 --> 00:39:43.923
WHEREABOUTS UNKNOWN

624
00:39:44.006 --> 00:39:45.925
MISSING

625
00:39:46.008 --> 00:39:48.010
[mysterious music intensifies]

626
00:39:52.932 --> 00:39:53.974
[gasps softly]

627
00:39:54.058 --> 00:39:58.145
MISSING
REN TSUTSUMIDA

628
00:39:58.229 --> 00:40:00.231
[mysterious music continues]

629
00:40:07.738 --> 00:40:09.740
- [horn blares]
- [music stops]

630
00:40:13.869 --> 00:40:15.329
[newscaster] <i>Our top story.</i>

631
00:40:16.247 --> 00:40:18.749
News has recently emerged
about White Center.

632
00:40:18.833 --> 00:40:21.419
named by the Human Vapor
in his latest interview.

633
00:40:21.502 --> 00:40:24.964
- There was a social welfare facility…
- [phone vibrating]

634
00:40:25.047 --> 00:40:27.216
…which was based in Yamanashi Prefecture.

635
00:40:28.634 --> 00:40:30.136
[softly] Hello? Mr. Ozaki?

636
00:40:34.890 --> 00:40:36.225
That's not my real name.

637
00:40:36.725 --> 00:40:38.727
[newscaster continues in background]

638
00:40:39.562 --> 00:40:40.646
[Obata] <i>Ms. Kono.</i>

639
00:40:41.313 --> 00:40:45.317
I have a journal in my possession
that details my time at White Center.

640
00:40:46.402 --> 00:40:48.070
It lists all the crimes committed

641
00:40:48.154 --> 00:40:50.781
by the individuals
at the head of the facility.

642
00:40:51.615 --> 00:40:52.533
And…

643
00:40:54.452 --> 00:40:57.121
I'd like to hand the journal over to you.
if you'll take it?

644
00:40:57.204 --> 00:40:59.582
- [solemn piano music playing]
- [breathes deeply]

645
00:41:01.000 --> 00:41:02.460
That means the world.

646
00:41:03.919 --> 00:41:05.463
Thank you for your courage.

647
00:41:07.506 --> 00:41:10.217
My life has been a lie.
and I'm sick of it.

648
00:41:11.135 --> 00:41:14.263
I'm tired of the lies
and I'm tired of hating myself.

649
00:41:15.723 --> 00:41:18.476
- Can I see you now. please?
- <i>Yes. of course.</i>

650
00:41:19.059 --> 00:41:20.186
Now is fine.

651
00:41:22.563 --> 00:41:23.898
Where would you like to meet?

652
00:41:23.981 --> 00:41:26.192
[music becomes suspenseful]

653
00:41:29.195 --> 00:41:30.446
[exhales]

654
00:41:34.158 --> 00:41:35.159
[sighs]

655
00:41:36.869 --> 00:41:38.871
[music fades out]

656
00:41:40.789 --> 00:41:41.957
[Shota] Mr. Ozaki.

657
00:41:44.627 --> 00:41:45.794
Hello. Shota.

658
00:41:50.883 --> 00:41:52.051
I couldn't sleep.

659
00:41:52.551 --> 00:41:54.094
I was up all night thinking.

660
00:41:58.307 --> 00:41:59.308
I can't do it.

661
00:41:59.391 --> 00:42:01.477
I can't tell the truth like you said.

662
00:42:03.521 --> 00:42:04.772
I…

663
00:42:06.732 --> 00:42:08.442
I don't want to keep lying.

664
00:42:10.486 --> 00:42:13.739
And I don't want to be like the bullies
who pick on Yoshitsune.

665
00:42:18.661 --> 00:42:19.828
But I'm scared.

666
00:42:20.913 --> 00:42:22.498
I'm not brave enough.

667
00:42:26.168 --> 00:42:27.962
Sorry for disappointing you. sir.

668
00:42:34.343 --> 00:42:35.386
Shota.

669
00:42:39.014 --> 00:42:40.349
I understand.

670
00:42:46.272 --> 00:42:48.023
Being brave's not easy.

671
00:42:51.151 --> 00:42:52.486
There's still time.

672
00:42:54.697 --> 00:42:56.991
[soft. poignant music playing]

673
00:42:57.074 --> 00:42:58.117
[sniffs]

674
00:43:03.247 --> 00:43:04.415
Thanks for your help.

675
00:43:06.875 --> 00:43:08.210
Have a good day.

676
00:43:28.856 --> 00:43:30.149
[sighs]

677
00:43:34.945 --> 00:43:36.947
[menacing music playing]

678
00:43:41.285 --> 00:43:42.286
Hey!

679
00:43:46.624 --> 00:43:48.208
Looks like they're heading out.

680
00:43:56.175 --> 00:43:57.259
[Kenji] Let's go.

681
00:44:00.846 --> 00:44:02.848
[music fades out]

682
00:44:11.106 --> 00:44:13.901
- I guess he hasn't arrived yet.
- Yeah.

683
00:44:16.070 --> 00:44:17.780
I can get us something to drink.

684
00:44:31.752 --> 00:44:34.880
[breathes deeply]

685
00:44:36.715 --> 00:44:38.967
[low. tense music playing]

686
00:44:58.237 --> 00:45:00.614
- Tatsuya. come on. let's go.
- What's wrong?

687
00:45:02.449 --> 00:45:03.325
Wait.

688
00:45:05.786 --> 00:45:06.829
Wait up!

689
00:45:09.331 --> 00:45:11.458
We can't meet here.
Call Obata. let him know.

690
00:45:12.000 --> 00:45:13.669
- What?
- Hurry.

691
00:45:15.170 --> 00:45:16.130
Okay.

692
00:45:17.339 --> 00:45:19.383
[tense music continues]

693
00:45:20.217 --> 00:45:21.176
Come on.

694
00:45:23.887 --> 00:45:25.681
[music intensifies]

695
00:45:28.183 --> 00:45:29.268
He's not there.

696
00:45:30.310 --> 00:45:31.603
Start running.

697
00:45:31.687 --> 00:45:32.604
Right.

698
00:45:36.525 --> 00:45:38.110
- [man 1 grunts]
- [pedestrians yell]

699
00:45:43.949 --> 00:45:45.617
- Through here!
- [man 1] Outta my way!

700
00:45:45.701 --> 00:45:46.952
[man 2] Stop!

701
00:45:47.035 --> 00:45:48.829
- [Kyoko whimpers]
- Stop! Hey!

702
00:45:49.455 --> 00:45:51.206
- [man 2] Move!
- [man 3] They went down!

703
00:45:51.290 --> 00:45:52.666
[man 2] Fucking move!

704
00:45:53.751 --> 00:45:55.169
- [man 4] Whoa!
- [woman squeals]

705
00:45:55.252 --> 00:45:57.337
- Tatsuya!
- [Tatsuya] Sorry!

706
00:45:58.881 --> 00:46:00.883
[Kyoko panting]

707
00:46:02.092 --> 00:46:03.469
[man 2] Get back here!

708
00:46:05.387 --> 00:46:06.680
[Kyoko yells]

709
00:46:06.764 --> 00:46:08.098
[man 2 grunts]

710
00:46:08.182 --> 00:46:09.850
- [man 3 yelps]
- [Kyoko whimpers]

711
00:46:15.647 --> 00:46:17.524
[motorbikes engines whirring]

712
00:46:29.161 --> 00:46:30.746
[Tatsuya] Kyoko. what do we do?

713
00:46:32.289 --> 00:46:33.290
[man 5] Gimme that!

714
00:46:38.295 --> 00:46:40.881
Hey! Here! Take it.

715
00:46:41.673 --> 00:46:43.050
[man 5] Where'd you put it?

716
00:46:43.675 --> 00:46:45.761
- What?
- Where the fuck is it?

717
00:46:48.889 --> 00:46:50.724
[man 6] We're not gonna ask again.

718
00:46:53.977 --> 00:46:55.312
[breathes shakily]

719
00:46:57.397 --> 00:46:58.816
[man 6] Tell us where it is.

720
00:46:59.316 --> 00:47:01.777
- You wanna die? Huh? Tell us!
- [tires screech]

721
00:47:02.486 --> 00:47:04.238
Police! Drop your weapon!

722
00:47:06.782 --> 00:47:08.575
- [man 3] Quick. grab her!
- [gunshot]

723
00:47:08.659 --> 00:47:10.160
[man 3] Let's get outta here!

724
00:47:10.244 --> 00:47:11.787
[Kyoko] Get off of me!

725
00:47:11.870 --> 00:47:14.706
- Get in the fuckin' car!
- [man 3] They're still down.

726
00:47:14.790 --> 00:47:16.375
- [woman] Get in!
- [Kyoko squeals]

727
00:47:19.711 --> 00:47:21.213
[grunting]

728
00:47:23.423 --> 00:47:24.341
Abe!

729
00:47:28.095 --> 00:47:29.054
[tires screech]

730
00:47:30.013 --> 00:47:32.933
[grunts. breathes heavily]

731
00:47:44.570 --> 00:47:46.530
[gun clicks repeatedly]

732
00:47:46.613 --> 00:47:47.614
[man 6] Oh shit.

733
00:47:51.201 --> 00:47:52.953
[grunting]

734
00:47:54.580 --> 00:47:56.331
[grunting]

735
00:47:56.915 --> 00:47:58.834
[choking]

736
00:48:01.420 --> 00:48:03.422
[music fades]

737
00:48:06.216 --> 00:48:07.259
[Kenji] Kyoko.

738
00:48:07.801 --> 00:48:08.802
You okay?

739
00:48:11.930 --> 00:48:14.016
[Kyoko breathes shakily]

740
00:48:25.611 --> 00:48:27.404
I thought they were gonna kill us.

741
00:48:29.364 --> 00:48:31.950
Why would the yakuza be going after you?

742
00:48:33.619 --> 00:48:35.162
You do anything to piss them off?

743
00:48:35.245 --> 00:48:36.330
Yakuza?

744
00:48:38.498 --> 00:48:39.791
No. nothing.

745
00:48:40.459 --> 00:48:43.045
I was meeting
the ex-director of the White Center.

746
00:48:44.004 --> 00:48:46.048
He was gonna bring all his records.

747
00:48:46.131 --> 00:48:47.966
[rapid footsteps approaching]

748
00:48:48.050 --> 00:48:49.426
Kyoko! You okay?

749
00:48:49.509 --> 00:48:51.178
[Tatsuya panting]

750
00:48:51.929 --> 00:48:54.181
I recorded it. I got the whole thing!

751
00:48:54.264 --> 00:48:55.891
[Kyoko] I'm fine. Good job.

752
00:48:57.476 --> 00:48:59.436
You were meeting an informant. huh?

753
00:49:00.395 --> 00:49:04.358
That explains why they were after you.
doesn't it? Because of him.

754
00:49:05.609 --> 00:49:06.735
Where is he now?

755
00:49:17.037 --> 00:49:18.121
Obata's in danger!

756
00:49:18.205 --> 00:49:20.207
[tense. dramatic music playing]

757
00:49:35.681 --> 00:49:37.683
[music softens]

758
00:49:45.983 --> 00:49:47.275
[sighs]

759
00:49:55.784 --> 00:49:56.827
[Obata] Ah.

760
00:49:56.910 --> 00:49:58.078
Your car broke down?

761
00:49:58.578 --> 00:49:59.538
Yeah.

762
00:49:59.621 --> 00:50:03.083
My insurance is sending a car.
but they said it would take a while.

763
00:50:03.834 --> 00:50:06.920
There's a little repair shop
not too far back down the road.

764
00:50:07.004 --> 00:50:08.672
I could call them for you?

765
00:50:08.755 --> 00:50:11.008
[man] Thank you.
That would be very helpful.

766
00:50:11.091 --> 00:50:13.593
- [phone vibrates]
- I'm sorry. Excuse me for a moment.

767
00:50:13.677 --> 00:50:14.511
[man] Yes. sir.

768
00:50:18.223 --> 00:50:19.099
[Obata] Hello?

769
00:50:20.267 --> 00:50:21.309
Ms. Kono?

770
00:50:22.436 --> 00:50:23.603
Where are you right now?

771
00:50:24.646 --> 00:50:28.275
[Obata] <i>Unfortunately I was delayed</i>
<i>slightly. but I'm on my way now.</i>

772
00:50:28.358 --> 00:50:29.860
No! Stay where you are.

773
00:50:30.360 --> 00:50:33.155
We'll send some officers
to pick you up as soon as we can.

774
00:50:33.739 --> 00:50:35.615
Don't move. You're in serious danger.

775
00:50:38.702 --> 00:50:40.287
I'm not afraid of death.

776
00:50:41.038 --> 00:50:42.789
Not after what I've been through.

777
00:50:42.873 --> 00:50:44.332
[steam hissing]

778
00:50:44.416 --> 00:50:48.211
But I don't want to die before I've had
the chance to make things right.

779
00:50:50.922 --> 00:50:53.258
Undo some of the pain I caused.

780
00:50:56.053 --> 00:50:57.137
What pain?

781
00:50:58.096 --> 00:50:59.347
[Obata] <i>White Center.</i>

782
00:51:00.515 --> 00:51:04.019
<i>It may have been intended</i>
<i>to help society's most vulnerable.</i>

783
00:51:04.519 --> 00:51:06.563
<i>but that's not what it became.</i>

784
00:51:08.356 --> 00:51:10.984
<i>We did not help them. We used them.</i>

785
00:51:11.735 --> 00:51:13.945
<i>We turned them into human fuel.</i>

786
00:51:15.155 --> 00:51:17.866
Sorry. what do you mean. "human fuel"?

787
00:51:20.327 --> 00:51:22.579
[tense. dramatic music continues]

788
00:51:22.662 --> 00:51:25.582
The people who took over White Center
were ruthless.

789
00:51:28.043 --> 00:51:30.420
The director tried to oppose them.
and they shot him.

790
00:51:32.255 --> 00:51:33.799
<i>I was working there.</i>

791
00:51:35.258 --> 00:51:37.344
<i>They made me the new director.</i>

792
00:51:38.970 --> 00:51:40.806
<i>And they were very clear.</i>

793
00:51:40.889 --> 00:51:42.432
<i>The residents of White Center.</i>

794
00:51:42.516 --> 00:51:43.850
<i>the marginalized.</i>

795
00:51:44.351 --> 00:51:45.727
<i>the homeless.</i>

796
00:51:46.603 --> 00:51:49.606
the orphans with nowhere left to go.
no families…

797
00:51:51.733 --> 00:51:55.195
that they deserved to be sacrificed
in the name of progress.

798
00:51:55.737 --> 00:51:57.239
Human fuel.

799
00:52:03.537 --> 00:52:04.704
Mr. Obata.

800
00:52:06.456 --> 00:52:09.000
You know who was responsible. don't you?

801
00:52:10.752 --> 00:52:12.754
[wind blowing]

802
00:52:13.630 --> 00:52:15.966
An organization called Mufu.

803
00:52:17.676 --> 00:52:19.928
I have records
that detail Mufu's involvement.

804
00:52:20.011 --> 00:52:21.346
- [soft thud]
- [Obata grunts]

805
00:52:22.389 --> 00:52:23.515
[Obata groans]

806
00:52:24.683 --> 00:52:27.227
- [dramatic music playing]
- [Obata whimpers]

807
00:52:27.310 --> 00:52:28.854
Mufu's what?

808
00:52:29.563 --> 00:52:30.605
I don't…

809
00:52:31.189 --> 00:52:32.399
Mr. Obata. please…

810
00:52:32.482 --> 00:52:33.650
[pained groaning]

811
00:52:34.151 --> 00:52:35.652
[Kyoko] Mr. Obata?

812
00:52:35.735 --> 00:52:36.820
Are you still there?

813
00:52:36.903 --> 00:52:37.863
[Obata grunts]

814
00:52:38.655 --> 00:52:39.865
Mr. Obata!

815
00:52:39.948 --> 00:52:43.118
[Obata grunts and gasps]

816
00:52:43.910 --> 00:52:44.828
[yells]

817
00:52:44.911 --> 00:52:46.163
[Obata grunting]

818
00:52:50.083 --> 00:52:51.334
[Kyoko] <i>Are you okay?</i>

819
00:52:51.418 --> 00:52:53.003
<i>- What's going on?</i>
- [strained yell]

820
00:52:53.086 --> 00:52:54.087
Mr. Obata!

821
00:52:54.171 --> 00:52:56.256
[man yells wildly]

822
00:52:56.339 --> 00:52:58.758
Finally! I got you. asshole!

823
00:52:58.842 --> 00:53:00.760
Burn in hell. you bastard!

824
00:53:01.344 --> 00:53:02.596
You son of a bitch!

825
00:53:02.679 --> 00:53:04.097
Burn in hell! [yells]

826
00:53:04.181 --> 00:53:05.098
Mr. Obata!

827
00:53:05.599 --> 00:53:07.058
Are you okay?!

828
00:53:07.559 --> 00:53:09.561
[dramatic music continues]

829
00:53:10.896 --> 00:53:13.398
WHITE CENTER
WORK JOURNAL

830
00:53:13.481 --> 00:53:15.609
- [Obata whimpers]
- [Kyoko] <i>Say something!</i>

831
00:53:16.276 --> 00:53:17.527
<i>Mr. Obata?</i>

832
00:53:18.069 --> 00:53:19.571
[Obata groans weakly]

833
00:53:23.491 --> 00:53:25.243
- [Obata gasps]
- [Kyoko] <i>What happened?</i>

834
00:53:25.327 --> 00:53:28.330
<i>What's going on? Mr. Obata? Are you okay?</i>

835
00:53:29.080 --> 00:53:31.458
[dramatic music intensifies]

836
00:53:38.298 --> 00:53:40.300
[music ends]

837
00:53:41.760 --> 00:53:43.762
[dark. dramatic music playing]

838
00:53:44.305 --> 00:54:44.308
